NAME
LE_init - initialize the log-error messaging module

SYNOPSIS
#include <infr.h>
void LE_init (int argc, char **argv);

DESCRIPTION
LE_init passes the command line arguments to the LE module. The process 
name and the "-L" option are parsed. If an LB is used for output, 
LE_lb_name and LE_init must be called before calling LE_send_msg. If no 
LB output is needed, LE_init call is optional. If LE_init is not called, 
however, the process_name part in the "text" field will be missing.

LE_init can only be called once. The second call to this function will
be ignored.

